text: The autocorrect has been pretty awful for about a month now. I've waited for an update to fix it, and the recent one sort of helped, but it's still "correcting" words into completely different words (like when I type "hi" it will turn into "him" or "his" when I press space for the next word, or "into" will turn into "I told," among other random assumptions). On top of "correcting" words into different ones altogether, there will be a few typos that it will refuse to correct at all on random occasions (I just typed "efuse" in that sentence and it did not even offer "refuse" as a word to correct to). I have a Samsung S5 if it helps any, and I have had and loved this app for a few years now. I don't want to give it up, but it has become very difficult to deal with retyping everything over and over again.
